Description: Very small fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows flat area with wood impressions, a second side shows a string impression. The front has parts of an oval scarab-like impression preserved. Finger impressions on top of the seal impression distort the motif slightly but it seems to shows a kheper in the middle with an upright cobra (?) to the right of it, facing inwards.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
